    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped to Gradation 1 per MRL 2 requirements and not formally assessed. Validation results for pressure rise and wall shear stress include structured uncertainty quantification. The relative hemolysis index comparison (VR-01) characterizes aleatory uncertainty qualitatively based on published biological variability ranges; while this approach was deemed sufficient by the assessment team for MRL 2, it does not provide a structured probabilistic UQ link. Overall credibility evidence supports acceptance of the CFD model for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
